flower_class=[]
img_set=[]

for i in ls:
    print(i)
    for image in (os.listdir('Desktop/data/plant-seedlings-classification/train/'+i)):
        instance_name.append(image)
        flower_class.append(i)
        img_set.append(cv2.imread('Desktop/data/plant-seedlings-classification/train/'+i+"/"+image))

#random images and display images along with its species
def show_randoms(n):
    random_num=np.random.randint(0,4751,n)
    print(random_num)
    
    for i in random_num:
        img=flower_db['img_set'][i]
        img=cv2.cvtColor(img,cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        plt.matshow(img)
        plt.xlabel(flower_db['flower_class'][i])
        
show_randoms(6)

Model training¶

In [18]:
X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(normalized_X_train,y_train,test_size=0.162,random_state=100)
In [19]:
#CNN architecture to train the model
con_nn=models.Sequential([
    layers.Conv2D(filters=64,kernel_size=(3,3),activation='softmax', input_shape=(160, 160, 3)),
    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(12, activation='softmax')    
])

con_nn.compile(optimizer='adam',loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])
